🚀Pika World Markets Update - 11 Jan 2024🚀🎢Equity markets were broadly higher as investors await the latest CPI data to be released tonight.The Nasdaq rose for the fourth day with major corporate news and economic outlook. The S&P 500 is still unable to break the new high achieved in January 2022. Let's get into the details.💰Amazon shares rose after the company announced cost-cutting plans through retrenching hundreds of jobs in some segments of its business in Twitch: film and television studios.📖The 1o-Year note saw its yield rise marginally to 4.029% after a weak auction  and this could spell trouble for future tranches should continued weak demand affect the large supply of bills given the large fiscal deficit of the US government.🎙We heard New York Fed President Williams speaking in a hawkish tone on the monetary policy  sending chilling effects to the doves expecting massive rate cuts. He is expecting the same mantra of longer for higher in terms of the Fed Funds rate and that inflation  while down  will still need more evidence that prices are trending down on a sustainable path.Based on the CME FedWatch Tool  which tracks the Fed's fed rate probabilities  traders are pricing in 64.5% of the first rate cut in the March FOMC meeting. His comments dampen the major index towards the close.📱Meta is rising towards the highest close since September 2021. Positive sentiments circled the company  given the expectation that revenue from WhatsApp could see remarkable growth that flourished with the adoption of artificial intelligence to help automate customer service programs.💡What's on the menu today?🖨It's the inflation data day for CPI . We expect a rise from 0.1% growth in the prior quarter to accelerate to 0.2%. However  on an annual basis  we expect a continued downward trend from 4% to 3.8%.Analysts will be looking closely at shelter costs  given the stickiness of rental expenses contributing to a large chunk of the inflation narrative. A downward trend in that figure will provide relief for the market.It is 11 Jan  Thursday  9 am in Singapore and 9 pm in New York. Given a relatively resilient market  we are now seeing major indices at a pivotal point.We hope you have a splendid day at work and in school. I will catch up with you near the CPI data release hours.Cheers Pika Nat.🧃
